						<div class="postbody">I think if the scrolling is set to the nametable mirrors, it would not trigger A12 changes while rendering, since that's not part of the bits used when fetching from the nametables.  But I'm just guessing.  Has anyone scrolled to the palette area with rendering enabled?  I'd guess it would just act like a nametable mirror if rendering is enabled.
<br />
<br />When you set the VRAM address to the palette when rendering is off, it draws the color you are pointing to.</div>

					
